econet-eth: WHNAT downstream half-offload (F2+F3) -- WiFi egress mux

WiFi HW-NAT half-offload, phases 2 and 3 (econet-eth side). Completes the
downstream path (internet -> WiFi client) on top of the F1 vif registry (384).

F2 (en75_flow_offload_replace): when the flowtable offers a flow whose egress
smac is a registered mt76 AP vif (en75_whnat_idx_by_mac), build the FoE entry
for HALF-OFFLOAD instead of the dp=1 switch path -- dest_port = force-to-CPU
(en75_ppe_fcpu_dp) + a magic VLAN (vlan1 = vif index, etype 0x5678). The engine
does the NAT/PPPoE rewrite then bounces the frame to the CPU (crsn=0x16) with
that tag riding along.

F3 (en75_qdma_rx_process_one): extend the force-to-CPU delivery -- read the
inserted tag's TCI; if it indexes a registered WiFi vif (en75_whnat_vif_by_idx)
strip the tag and dev_queue_xmit to that BSS netdev (the OEM
PpeHitBindForceToWiFiHandler). The existing ethernet fixed-egress (fcpu_out)
path is preserved as the fallback. The CPU only does the final dev_xmit; the PPE
did the NAT, so the WiFi forward stops being bottlenecked by the 1-CPU MIPS.

The exact egress tag (entry etype 0x5678 vs VPM 0xF18 0x8100, and whether the
engine honors vlan1=idx as the TCI) is HW-empirical; F3 accepts both TPIDs and
keys off the TCI, to be confirmed on the bench.

